    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nBasically, the title. The Lua approach doesn't work, but Vimscript does.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Search any present word in the buffer. Say, with `/local<CR>`.\r\n2. Execute `:lua vim.v.hlsearch = 0`. Search highlighting doesn't disappear.\r\n3. Execute `:let v:hlsearch=0`. Search highlighting disappears.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nBoth approaches should act the same.\r\n\r\nNote: this might be the consequence of a note in `:h v:hlsearch` \"Note that the value is restored when returning from a function. |function-search-undo|\".\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-0aea8fa\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo (doesn't have this functionality)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64 (6.5.3-arch1-1)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst-0.9\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
